==English==

===Etymology===
From the town of the same name in the Western Cape, South Africa. During the South African War, (or [[Boer]] War), English officers who had done badly, were sent to a farm at Stellenbosch, without losing rank, to look after horses.

===Transitive verb===
'''stellenbosch'''

# ''South African, obsolete:'' To be shifted sideways.

